The paper deals with algorithms for sampling from data streams, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The use of weighted sampling is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and data mining (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the impact of finite precision arithmetic on the accuracy of the algorithm, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
